SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 6004
By Watson
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize the Bachman-McCoy
Farm on the occasion of the property being
placed in the National Register of Historic
Places.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that this General Assembly salute that most noble institution, the
family farm, which has served as a cornerstone of our communities for more than two centuries;
and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy family farm is the Bachman-McCoy Farm, which, upon
the nomination of the Tennessee Historical Commission, has been placed in the National
Register of Historic Places by the National Park Service of the United States Department of the
Interior; and
WHEREAS, this notable property is also listed in the Tennessee Register of Historic
Places; and
WHEREAS, located along historic Anderson Pike near the top of the famed W Road in
the Town of Walden on Signal Mountain, the Bachman-McCoy farm was listed in the National
Register for its association with significant events in American history, as Bachman family
members have played important roles in local politics, social reform causes, and environmental
preservation over the years; and
WHEREAS, in 1911, Nathan and Pearl Bachman purchased the property as a summer
home; by 1918, the Bachmans had transformed the property into a full-time residence and
gentleman's farm; and
WHEREAS, with the farm serving as his home base, Nathan L. Bachman rose in
prominence in Tennessee's political world; he served on the Tennessee Supreme Court and as
